      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LADY RAPID (7) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (30.35) at The Meadows behind Organised Crime in a Grade 4. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings two times from four starts. Makes plenty of appeal. CRIS TESSA (4) rocketed out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (34.90) at this track over 595m. Consistent performer from this draw with a win and four minor placings to her credit. Expected to be in the finish again. OKAY BOSS (1) missed the frame last time when fifth (30.18) at this track but prior to that had three placings in a row. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. Has ability and is one of the better chances. MANILA PANDA (2) is a last start winner who rates one of the chances again.",
